</div>
<hr local-id=3D"e9cb2d0eae7f">
<h2 local-id=3D"073723cde535" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-3.2Environment=
s">3.2 Environments</h2>
<p local-id=3D"2b463ca385e8">Each VPC represents a distinct environment wit=
h the following characteristics:</p>
<p local-id=3D"dd20acba8e32"><strong>HQ-1 (us-east-1) =E2=80=94 Primary Hea=
dquarters</strong><br>
The primary HQ environment hosts the core network boundary for the organisa=
tion. It peers with Office A, Office B, and HQ-2. Contains one public and t=
wo private subnets.</p>
<p local-id=3D"78efd0a54cf6"><strong>HQ-2 (us-east-1) =E2=80=94 Secondary H=
eadquarters</strong><br>
Acts as a secondary HQ environment, peered with Office C, Office D, and HQ-=
1. Contains one public and two private subnets.</p>
<p local-id=3D"cc89eaed00f2"><strong>Office A / B / C / D (us-east-2) =E2=
=80=94 Branch Offices</strong><br>
Each office is an isolated VPC representing a remote branch. Offices A and =
B are intra-region peered. Offices C and D are intra-region peered. Each co=
ntains one public and one private subnet.</p>
<p local-id=3D"86f2c460fdc9"><strong>PUBLIC SUBNETS (all VPCs)</strong><br>
Used for bastion hosts and internet-facing EC2 instances. Connected to an I=
nternet Gateway with a default route (0.0.0.0/0 =E2=86=92 IGW).</p>
<p local-id=3D"16beb2ac1a2d"><strong>PRIVATE SUBNETS (all VPCs)</strong><br=
>
Used for backend or internal services. No direct internet access. Traffic i=
s routed only via VPC Peering connections.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"d1d8d225cfe5">
<h2 local-id=3D"b3eb43a3559d" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-3.3ToolsandTec=
hnologies">3.3 Tools and Technologies</h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">AWS VPC=
             Core networking service for all environments
AWS EC2             Virtual instances for connectivity testing
AWS Internet        Gateway outbound internet access for public subnets
Gateway
AWS Route Tables    Traffic routing control per subnet tier
AWS Security        Instance-level firewall rules
Groups
AWS VPC Peering     Private inter-VPC connectivity
Python (boto3)      AWS SDK used for automation scripting
AWS Console         GUI used for environment setup and validation</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"26fe74daa527">
<h2 local-id=3D"6a133fb53a35" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-3.4Application=
Architecture&amp;UserRequestFlow">3.4 Application Architecture &amp; User R=
equest Flow</h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">INTERNE=
T
    |
[IGW - HQ-1]        [IGW - HQ-2]
    |                    |
[Public Subnet]     [Public Subnet]
    |                    |
[Private Subnets]   [Private Subnets]
    |                    |
VPC Peering          VPC Peering
|       |            |       |
[Off-A] [Off-B]    [Off-C] [Off-D]</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"344433211258">User request flow (example =E2=80=94 HQ to Off=
ice access):</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"626220379998">
<li local-id=3D"fadaef0500ad">
<p local-id=3D"9399a2d0bce8">Request originates from an EC2 instance in HQ-=
1 Public subnet</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"de470cf2d9dc">
<p local-id=3D"df10e74c3673">Traffic is routed via the HQ-1 route table to =
the VPC Peering connection pointing to the destination office VPC</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a20c4e9ee65b">
<p local-id=3D"16371d72e506">The peering connection forwards traffic to the=
 target VPC</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9701f5fff3ae">
<p local-id=3D"3b4280070c32">The target VPC's route table directs traffic t=
o the appropriate subnet and EC2 instance</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"10c61b8f5b80">
<p local-id=3D"c1466571eaa8">Security groups on the destination instance ev=
aluate and permit or deny the connection</p></li>
</ol>
<hr local-id=3D"4f00a73a636b">
<h1 local-id=3D"1392fa67493a" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-4.DEVELOPMENTP=
RACTICES">4. DEVELOPMENT PRACTICES</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"b94f0f6be4f7" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-4.1VersionCont=
rol">4.1 Version Control</h2>
<p local-id=3D"17580a22ce03">The automation script (boto3) developed for th=
is project was managed locally during the implementation phase. For product=
ion use, the recommended version control approach is:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"282b8ad2ad6d">
<li local-id=3D"099349d3dacf">
<p local-id=3D"4dd0fcb61867">Repository hosted on GitHub or AWS CodeCommit<=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"04b0924713ce">
<p local-id=3D"a89028cac62d">Branching strategy: main (stable) / develop (a=
ctive work)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b5819238002b">
<p local-id=3D"601891f82897">All infrastructure changes reviewed via pull r=
equest before merge to main</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3662d2dbfbb2">
<p local-id=3D"45f494b19e7e">Commit messages to follow conventional format =
describing the resource changed and the action taken</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"fed1f7998354">
<h2 local-id=3D"6059dbfb1426" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-4.2ContinuousI=
ntegration">4.2 Continuous Integration</h2>
<p local-id=3D"a0fd045f417b">For this implementation, infrastructure provis=
ioning was executed manually via the boto3 script and validated through the=
 AWS Console. In a production CI context, the recommended approach is:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"a02acaf86ec7">
<li local-id=3D"834a3cab5df4">
<p local-id=3D"ccd06ccadf9c">CI pipeline triggered on push to the develop b=
ranch</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d077512b2878">
<p local-id=3D"4da773f835a8">Pipeline stages: lint Python script =E2=86=92 =
validate AWS credentials =E2=86=92 dry-run provisioning check =E2=86=92 not=
ify engineer</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"690545b72396">
<p local-id=3D"500dba7e50e1">Tools: GitHub Actions or AWS CodePipeline</p><=
/li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"8f49a10a385f">
<h2 local-id=3D"3a43f2641f0c" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-4.3AutomatedTe=
sting">4.3 Automated Testing</h2>
<p local-id=3D"02d32b308f1a">Connectivity validation was performed manually=
 using telnet, ping, and SSH from EC2 instances. For a production-grade pip=
eline, the following automated testing approach is recommended:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"0807af39e409">
<li local-id=3D"036ccdaf0904">
<p local-id=3D"f39da9db011d">Unit tests on the boto3 script to verify resou=
rce creation logic and idempotency</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e79f58a0729c">
<p local-id=3D"3c3cf48af7f0">Integration tests that validate VPC peering st=
ate via AWS API after provisioning</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7f50108e7d1c">
<p local-id=3D"76c64571c234">End-to-end tests using scripted ping/telnet ch=
ecks from designated test instances</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"5ab1c984e93e">[See Section 9 - Artifacts: A15, A16, A17, A18=
]</p>
<hr local-id=3D"46ce1f575665">
<h2 local-id=3D"777f5c0ca7ac" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-4.4CodeQuality=
andAnalysis">4.4 Code Quality and Analysis</h2>
<p local-id=3D"f65db24e5d93">The boto3 automation script was written with t=
he following quality practices:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"91bc9a8e86fc">
<li local-id=3D"61f06182d576">
<p local-id=3D"7afe0f1c00e4">Idempotent functions =E2=80=94 each resource c=
hecks for existing state before creation to allow safe re-runs</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b44e6fd86a63">
<p local-id=3D"6ecf56cf18e5">Helper functions used for repeated operations =
(tag_resource, find_vpc, find_subnet) to reduce duplication</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"514f4ea00a6e">
<p local-id=3D"fcdbc15f3191">Exception handling on all peering operations t=
o prevent script failure on duplicate connection attempts</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d19ca6d3f5f1">
<p local-id=3D"e26b3aaec985">Clear section comments separating VPC, Subnet,=
 IGW, Route Table, and Peering logic</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"990a8d192873">[See Section 9 - Artifacts: A19]</p>
<hr local-id=3D"26c798121203">
<h1 local-id=3D"6e403f8703d4" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-5.DEPLOYMENTAN=
DRELEASEMANAGEMENT">5. DEPLOYMENT AND RELEASE MANAGEMENT</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"f1589f596bf5" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-5.1DeploymentS=
trategy">5.1 Deployment Strategy</h2>
<p local-id=3D"bcf1bc5e5cce">The infrastructure was deployed in a sequentia=
l, dependency-aware order to ensure each layer was available before the nex=
t was configured:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Phase 1=
 =E2=86=92 VPC creation (both regions)
Phase 2 =E2=86=92 Subnet provisioning per VPC
Phase 3 =E2=86=92 Internet Gateway creation and attachment
Phase 4 =E2=86=92 Route Table creation and subnet association
Phase 5 =E2=86=92 VPC Peering connection requests and acceptance
Phase 6 =E2=86=92 EC2 instance deployment
Phase 7 =E2=86=92 Connectivity validation testing</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"42a8f6c26a45">This approach mirrors a rolling deployment str=
ategy =E2=80=94 each component is brought online and verified before procee=
ding, minimising the risk of cascading configuration failures.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"515c56a931ec">
<h2 local-id=3D"4dae8a172abf" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-5.2Configurati=
onManagement">5.2 Configuration Management</h2>
<p local-id=3D"2b160687c43a">All infrastructure configuration is defined an=
d managed through the boto3 Python script, which serves as the Infrastructu=
re as Code (IaC) artifact for this project. Key configuration management pr=
actices applied:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"df77e3966d0f">
<li local-id=3D"d29bb791cd49">
<p local-id=3D"ba03889bdcaf">CIDR blocks, region names, and VPC names defin=
ed as variables at the top of the script for easy modification</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"dbc87d6cef02">
<p local-id=3D"323e1d898e57">Resource tagging applied to all created assets=
 for consistent identification across the AWS Console and CLI</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"88601ab34504">
<p local-id=3D"89704d629d23">Script designed for idempotent execution =E2=
=80=94 safe to re-run without creating duplicate resources</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"11646bdbc1fc">
<h2 local-id=3D"46a649867085" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-5.3ContinuousD=
elivery/Deployment">5.3 Continuous Delivery / Deployment</h2>
<p local-id=3D"2d2be8672f05">For this project, deployment was executed manu=
ally by running the boto3 script. For a production continuous delivery pipe=
line, the recommended workflow is:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">1. Engi=
neer pushes updated script to version control
2. CI pipeline validates the script (lint + dry-run)
3. Manual approval gate before infrastructure changes are applied to produc=
tion
4. Script executed via CD pipeline with output logged to AWS CloudWatch or =
a central log store
5. Post-deployment validation tests run automatically</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"dd50039facd6">
<h1 local-id=3D"e3b11dc25031" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-6.MONITORINGAN=
DINCIDENTMANAGEMENT">6. MONITORING AND INCIDENT MANAGEMENT</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"78bd6a497c90" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-6.1MonitoringT=
oolsandMetrics">6.1 Monitoring Tools and Metrics</h2>
<p local-id=3D"c60ec95d988d">For the current implementation, monitoring was=
 performed manually via the AWS Console during and after provisioning. For =
an ongoing production environment, the following monitoring stack is recomm=
ended:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"38c5b129a548">
<li local-id=3D"f67c4d65bcb1">
<p local-id=3D"2a22d69166f7">AWS CloudWatch: collect VPC Flow Logs, EC2 CPU=
/network metrics, and custom application metrics</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"812069cd5e66">
<p local-id=3D"a1056ec88fed">VPC Flow Logs: capture accepted and rejected t=
raffic at the network interface level for all subnets</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2b5d98a2bfec">
<p local-id=3D"9d3143d44fa5">AWS CloudTrail: audit all API calls made again=
st the infrastructure for governance and compliance</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"68666bd7a038">Key metrics to monitor:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"7107edd6afb8">
<li local-id=3D"fc95829227f8">
<p local-id=3D"2922a037dbb9">VPC peering connection state (Active / Deleted=
 / Expired)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7b568861c2fa">
<p local-id=3D"1bc7e6186a94">EC2 instance reachability and status checks</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"d83b69a18886">
<p local-id=3D"a022ca30b9a7">Network throughput and packet loss across peer=
ing connections</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"672e409feaf2">
<p local-id=3D"6a17d2b7ea1b">Rejected traffic in VPC Flow Logs (potential s=
ecurity events)</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"ecc73b788c3e">
<h2 local-id=3D"6a2306b4e9e8" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-6.2Alertingand=
Notification">6.2 Alerting and Notification</h2>
<p local-id=3D"9e6da647f686">Recommended alerting configuration for product=
ion use:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"5eac703f23f9">
<li local-id=3D"f01b0f588c0d">
<p local-id=3D"cee762429bd4">CloudWatch Alarms on EC2 status check failures=
 =E2=86=92 notify via SNS to on-call engineer</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cb451c1860b0">
<p local-id=3D"a3248de6f932">CloudWatch Alarms on VPC Flow Log rejected tra=
ffic spikes =E2=86=92 notify security team</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ca0de97700fd">
<p local-id=3D"de05afd6fd8f">Escalation path: on-call engineer =E2=86=92 te=
am lead =E2=86=92 architect for unresolved P1 incidents within 30 minutes</=
p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"5c0f94dfdea3">
<h2 local-id=3D"d81296e204f4" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-6.3IncidentMan=
agement">6.3 Incident Management</h2>
<p local-id=3D"ac54a940845c">Recommended incident management process:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">DETECTI=
ON   Alert triggered via CloudWatch or manual observation
LOGGING     Incident raised in ticketing system with severity, affected res=
ource, and initial diagnosis
TRIAGE      On-call engineer assesses scope and impact
RESOLUTION  Engineer isolates affected resource, applies fix, and validates=
 restoration
POST-MORTEM Root cause documented and preventive action identified within 4=
8 hours of resolution</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"2fcf25564570">Roles:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"2732dba1f5f3">
<li local-id=3D"5f3b07cd3d3a">
<p local-id=3D"c8b50dc4b5b8">DevOps Engineer: first responder, applies fix<=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d5e542de803b">
<p local-id=3D"ba23610c73a6">Solution Architect: consulted for network-laye=
r changes</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9e4ebf5d9c38">
<p local-id=3D"24c4472725b9">CTO: notified for P1 incidents affecting produ=
ction</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"a258802cfa9d">
<h1 local-id=3D"d42d5cdac3cb" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-7.SECURITY&amp=
;COMPLIANCE">7. SECURITY &amp; COMPLIANCE</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"6746c9ce23e3" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-Infrastructure=
Security">Infrastructure Security</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"e5ab712673db">
<li local-id=3D"127875455d75">
<p local-id=3D"b69bded1d75b">Each VPC is isolated by design =E2=80=94 no de=
fault inter-VPC routing</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3a58018059e3">
<p local-id=3D"5fcb6408bef2">Private subnets have no Internet Gateway route=
, preventing direct public access to backend resources</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"64973dcad55b">
<p local-id=3D"e0c60ba218ef">VPC Peering connections established only betwe=
en explicitly required pairs =E2=80=94 no transitive routing permitted</p><=
/li>
<li local-id=3D"ca79878f549d">
<p local-id=3D"2dc7884af268">Internet Gateways attached only to VPCs requir=
ing public subnet access</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2b24d51c8833">
<p local-id=3D"69421bc24d1e">All route tables reviewed to ensure no uninten=
ded routes</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"9fd833f29b5e">
<h2 local-id=3D"c7cbb270c2c1" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-IdentityandAcc=
essManagement">Identity and Access Management</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"cabedfb2f7de">
<li local-id=3D"ad06cfdc2b1a">
<p local-id=3D"2a2549be96d4">AWS Console access restricted to authorised te=
am members only</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7472180214c1">
<p local-id=3D"0877046e6a8b">boto3 script credentials (ACCESS_KEY / SECRET_=
KEY) must be rotated after use and never committed to version control</p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"b55860e65277">
<p local-id=3D"c50215869374">Recommended: replace static credentials with I=
AM Roles and instance profiles for production automation</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4d690df64088">
<p local-id=3D"90e9cbd44cb7">Principle of least privilege applied =E2=80=94=
 security groups permit only SSH (TCP 22) and ICMP from known VPC CIDR rang=
es</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5e6144b29ca1">
<p local-id=3D"c1223aa96d96">No 0.0.0.0/0 inbound rules on any security gro=
up</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"0aef757326ef">
<h1 local-id=3D"a8703b6845df" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-8.COSTOPTIMISA=
TION">8. COST OPTIMISATION</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"a436e3080dca" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-8.1InputsUsedt=
oEstimateSolutionCost">8.1 Inputs Used to Estimate Solution Cost</h2>
<p local-id=3D"a10bd2d30fc6">The following inputs were used to assess the c=
ost profile of this implementation:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"cc35b5b91e52">
<li local-id=3D"7b1e3b88d1a7">
<p local-id=3D"b7fa3631285d">6 VPCs across 2 regions (no charge for VPC cre=
ation)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"082da9a167f5">
<p local-id=3D"d781a515608c">7 VPC Peering connections<br>
 (intra-region: $0.01/GB data transfer;<br>
 cross-region: standard inter-region rates apply)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"52344d1d3e8f">
<p local-id=3D"a6d15db6c91a">12 EC2 t2.micro instances<br>
 (Free Tier eligible: 750 hrs/month combined)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"15096e4fd69c">
<p local-id=3D"56bad94ed07d">6 Internet Gateways<br>
 ($0.005/hr per IGW when attached + $0.09/GB data out)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"04d612f3073c">
<p local-id=3D"58adcfea0ba0">EBS storage for EC2 instances<br>
 (Free Tier: 30 GB/month)</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"2ecd8526e22c">For a validation-only deployment as implemente=
d, the majority of resources fall within AWS Free Tier limits.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"f44305151d6d">
<h2 local-id=3D"2a3c310bbd19" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-8.2SummaryofCo=
stEstimates">8.2 Summary of Cost Estimates</h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Resourc=
e              Qty   Est. Monthly Cost
--------------------  ----  -----------------
VPCs                  6     $0.00
VPC Peering (idle)    7     $0.00
EC2 t2.micro (FT)     12    $0.00 (Free Tier)
Internet Gateways     6     ~$2.16 (idle/month)
Data Transfer         --    Variable per usage
--------------------  ----  -----------------
ESTIMATED TOTAL             ~$2=E2=80=935/month (idle)</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"a7fba041745b">For a production environment with active workl=
oads, data transfer costs across peering connections and EC2 instance upgra=
des would represent the primary cost drivers.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"153625d3eaf9">
<h2 local-id=3D"45618ab85747" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-8.3BusinessVal=
ueAnalysis">8.3 Business Value Analysis</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"3e81e6be2a34">
<li local-id=3D"266f0f574879">
<p local-id=3D"9aaf256211c3">Eliminates the need for costly dedicated WAN l=
inks between office locations by leveraging AWS backbone networking</p></li=
>
<li local-id=3D"7aa4f08bf19f">
<p local-id=3D"a85e91862214">VPC Peering is significantly more cost-effecti=
ve than AWS Transit Gateway for point-to-point connectivity at this scale</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c6c22a53e3d4">
<p local-id=3D"d91a786299ce">The automation script reduces future provision=
ing time from hours to minutes, representing direct savings in engineer tim=
e</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"400f94be5224">
<p local-id=3D"a6330a8fd7f3">The isolated VPC design reduces compliance sco=
pe per environment, lowering audit and remediation costs</p></li>
</ul>
