<hr local-id=3D"9085af9c6cf2">
<h1 local-id=3D"d03b9cada765" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-10.IMPLEMENTAT=
IONTIMELINE">10. IMPLEMENTATION TIMELINE</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"be35adba79c9" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-10.1Milestones=
andDeliverables">10.1 Milestones and Deliverables</h2>
<p local-id=3D"596d41cc41ca"><strong>Phase 1: Network Design &amp; Planning=
</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"5f92157ae0e3">
<li local-id=3D"704bb8b59e80">
<p local-id=3D"7974f3582f07">CIDR block allocation for all 6 VPCs</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"efd2290bbaf2">
<p local-id=3D"5c9c35f90802">Subnet sizing and segmentation plan</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"02d3291236ed">
<p local-id=3D"a35adb7fc426">Peering topology definition<br>
Duration: 1 day</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"bdcd51e302e0"><strong>Phase 2: Infrastructure Provisioning</=
strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"063ff5bc6777">
<li local-id=3D"00c94345c7cb">
<p local-id=3D"530dac3acc43">VPC, Subnet, IGW, and Route Table creation</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"5e9b8fad1d38">
<p local-id=3D"c6ccadc4b2b7">VPC Peering connection setup (cross-region and=
 intra-region)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b6e10defc2af">
<p local-id=3D"842cc0d4b512">EC2 instance deployment in all environments<br=
>
Duration: 2 days</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"8d928439d5bf"><strong>Phase 3: Validation &amp; Testing</str=
ong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"117f0e0ebd52">
<li local-id=3D"03f09efbf471">
<p local-id=3D"266c39fe6b3b">Telnet, ping, and SSH connectivity testing</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"9b1b7d47e246">
<p local-id=3D"4a5e4c4dfb37">Controlled failure testing for non-peered rout=
es</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f82c058bbdd5">
<p local-id=3D"5811c2f0140c">Security group review and hardening<br>
Duration: 1 day</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"4c90f085618b"><strong>Phase 4: Automation &amp; Documentatio=
n</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"9631e0df1f9e">
<li local-id=3D"0a2ff7ed8241">
<p local-id=3D"bdcb5acd681d">boto3 automation script development and testin=
g</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bace55292302">
<p local-id=3D"029459940d24">Technical documentation preparation<br>
Duration: 1 day</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"f88fe1087f70">Final Delivery: All environments validated, do=
cumentation complete, automation script delivered</p>
<hr local-id=3D"1a79a00e5f46">
<h1 local-id=3D"43a03150bbc8" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-11.CONTINUOUSI=
MPROVEMENT">11. CONTINUOUS IMPROVEMENT</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"da62f8bd9f56" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-11.1Feedbackan=
dRetrospectives">11.1 Feedback and Retrospectives</h2>
<p local-id=3D"7c937339a120">The following mechanisms are recommended for o=
ngoing feedback collection and retrospective review:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"32554fe2fb43">
<li local-id=3D"02e7297374c9">
<p local-id=3D"bfe9e59ec09f">Post-implementation review meeting with all st=
akeholders within one week of delivery to capture immediate feedback</p></l=
i>
<li local-id=3D"9b00a3601b09">
<p local-id=3D"fa16de5a3f92">Structured retrospective covering: what worked=
 well, what could be improved, and action items with owners</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c2dff396f640">
<p local-id=3D"1ff0138076d0">Feedback from DevOps engineers on script usabi=
lity and any manual steps that could be further automated</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"99318e586628">
<p local-id=3D"b12a188989f1">Review of VPC Flow Logs post-deployment to ide=
ntify any unexpected traffic patterns or misconfigured routes</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"6f90fac1395d">
<h2 local-id=3D"4f761bf00fdc" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-11.2IterativeE=
nhancements">11.2 Iterative Enhancements</h2>
<p local-id=3D"72884928951a">The following enhancements are identified for =
future iterations based on current architecture limitations:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"dee0a988afe5">
<li local-id=3D"3c93f6e5af81">
<p local-id=3D"8416bbf96a57">Replace static IAM credentials in the boto3 sc=
ript with IAM Roles to improve security posture</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"99093139ec3b">
<p local-id=3D"1c5bf4de1dfe">Introduce AWS Transit Gateway if the number of=
 VPC connections grows beyond manageable peering pairs</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"eade95b14b92">
<p local-id=3D"103e1fe7824d">Add NAT Gateway to private subnets for control=
led outbound internet access where required</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d3c57079e630">
<p local-id=3D"6dcbca4d0833">Implement VPC Flow Logs and CloudWatch dashboa=
rds for ongoing network visibility</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"775ab970950b">
<p local-id=3D"e6a6f39f9299">Expand the automation script to cover EC2 depl=
oyment, security group creation, and post-provisioning validation</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d71de24b8600">
<p local-id=3D"943bded75db9">Introduce Terraform or AWS CDK as a long-term =
IaC replacement for the current boto3 script</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"b98f07e21524">
<h1 local-id=3D"1597fe4e6dc9" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-12.CONCLUSION"=
>12. CONCLUSION</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"f829228e5cd6" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-12.1Summary">1=
2.1 Summary</h2>
<p local-id=3D"f4cd7c0983da">This document has detailed the complete design=
 and implementation of a Multi-VPC AWS Network Environment spanning two reg=
ions. The solution delivers six isolated VPCs with structured CIDR allocati=
on, public and private subnet segmentation, and seven VPC Peering connectio=
ns enabling controlled inter-environment communication.</p>
<p local-id=3D"78dad75a9948">All connectivity paths were validated through =
telnet, ping, and SSH testing. Controlled failure testing confirmed that tr=
affic between non-peered VPCs is correctly blocked. The implementation adhe=
res to AWS Well-Architected Framework principles across all six pillars, an=
d a Python boto3 automation script was delivered for repeatable future prov=
isioning.</p>
<p local-id=3D"1a79d2adaebb">The architecture reflects a real-world enterpr=
ise cloud network design and provides a scalable foundation for production =
workload deployment.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"297cbe5a0886">
<h2 local-id=3D"1be522d03f0f" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-12.2NextSteps"=
>12.2 Next Steps</h2>
<p local-id=3D"757ed709f4c7">The following actions are recommended to conti=
nue maturing this implementation:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"b9220f07b4a7">
<li local-id=3D"4fd0f75ff242">
<p local-id=3D"fbc32ec1aa29">Review and implement the iterative enhancement=
s listed in Section 11.2</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"255a608c6f51">
<p local-id=3D"1080ffce90a0">Conduct a formal AWS Well-Architected Review a=
gainst the deployed environment</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a52114b69e7c">
<p local-id=3D"2153f68f1de3">Onboard monitoring via AWS CloudWatch and VPC =
Flow Logs</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6b5ac45d5ed8">
<p local-id=3D"e65c3a5c0bd1">Explore AWS Transit Gateway for simplified con=
nectivity as the environment scales</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9b4ccd9e2706">
<p local-id=3D"ba18936378c4">Schedule a 30-day post-implementation review w=
ith all stakeholders</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"a83c88659216">
<h1 local-id=3D"21adda5a2142" id=3D"Task17-TechnicalDocument-13.CUSTOMERACK=
NOWLEDGEMENT">13. CUSTOMER ACKNOWLEDGEMENT</h1>
